<Author>Auscaz
<Content>Absolutely fantastic We stayed at The Mandala Suites for three nights last week and it was fantastic. It is situated in Friederichstrasse (?spelling), within a short stroll of the Brandenburg Gate, Checkpoint Charlie etc. I chose it because of its close proximity to the fabulous Gendaremenmarkt Christmas market. The apartment was spacious and fully selfcontained. There is no washing machine/dryer in the apartment itself however apparently there is a laundry for guests in the basement of the building. Breakfast is served on the 8th floor every morning. From memory I think we paid around ten euro for 24 hours on the internet, which was far better than the 22 euro we paid for 24 hours in our hotel in Leipzig! At 130 euro per night, it was outstanding value for money and we would definitely stay there again next time.There is an awesome bakery about 20 metres up the road that opens at 7am and sells great coffee and an amazing array of breads/cakes etc. 
