<Author>tami01
<Content>Good and central location with minor flaws The Mandala Suites are centrally located at Friedrichstrasse Berlin, the destination of all luxury addicted travellers who are visiting the German capital. The hotel is part of a larger atrium office building and not well known with Berlin taxi drivers - so better be prepared to know the address. Very Small lobby  friendly service. The rooms are starting at 40 sqm up to more than 80 sqm - all with kitchen. No extremly stylish furniture - discreet elegance might a proper description. Comfortable beds, ok--ish bathrooms. No extravaganza. Wireless and LAN costs 10 鈧?a day. The six day access is for 30 鈧?- easly calculation what is the better choice. Connectivity inbound is ok, outbond can be a catastrophy, if you are not only checking your emails on the internet but work with an application such as Outlook, Lotus Notes etc. Room orientation varies pretty much - some are towards the glass attrium, which is a really calm place, others have windows and balconies to Friedrichstrasse (noisy) or attached streets (rel. noisy as well). Breakfast room on the 8th floor has very modern interieur, but - far too less tables. It can easly happen to you that you have to sit on the couch and wait for several minutes to get a table - unpleaseant, when you have time pressure.Buffet is good to very good, extras such as eggs or orange juice will be served at order. Long serving hours for people who like to sleep longer. View towards Potsdamer Platz, Reichstag, Siegessaeule etc. is impressive. Fitness room and sauna available at the same floor. In a nutshell:+Centrally located for business, getting around and upper class shopping+Good breakfast and beds+Possible tricky internet connectivitySolid, but nothing to fall in love with. Will try the Mandala Hotel at Potsdamer Platz or the SAS Radisson next time. 
