<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Home from home in the heart of Berlin This is not your ordinary hotel. What this facility offers is a large number of suites. I paid 鈧?09 a night for a suite that was bigger than my own flat. It was brand new, with two bedrooms, a sitting room, a wonderful bathroom and a fully equiped kitchen. I also had a nice balcony over a courtyard.If you like bellboys, and room service, and concierges then shoot for another hotel. However, if you are in Berlin for more than a couple of days, I would seriously consider staying here. It couldn't be better located, being as it is situated on the Friedrichstrasse, opposite Gendarmenmarkt. You have some of the best restaurants in town on your doorstep but if they don't tickle your fancy, you have your own kitchen.If ever I go to Berlin (at least five times a year) this is where I stay. But hush, don't tell everybody. 
